<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41bfrd"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41bfrd">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41bfrd">back flyleaf recto(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> little folks gloves</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">So the particular flower that the <mark>&ldquo;little folks&rdquo; used came to be called &ldquo;folks&apos; gloves.&rdquo;</mark> Then, because the country people were rough and clumsy in their talk, the name was shortened into &ldquo;Fox-gloves,&rdquo; the name that everyone uses now. <small> Miss Isa Bowman, <a name="IBSL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#IBSL"><cite title="source">The Story Of Lewis Carroll</cite></a>. (1899) 74-5</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
